sec.p:
α-Glucosidase inhibition was assessed as per Artanti et al.27 Samples (amount 0.1 mL) were added to test tube containing 0.1 mL 20 mM pNPG (p-nitrophenyl α-d-glucopyranoside) and 100 mM PBS (2.2 mL) at pH 7 followed by incubating it at 37°C for 5 minutes. The reaction was initiated by addition of 0.1 mL enzyme solution (1 mg/0.1 mL), followed 15 minutes' incubation at 37°C. The reaction was stopped by addition of 200 mM Na2CO3 (2.5 mL). Absorbance of p-nitrophenol released from p-nitrophenyl α-d-glucopyranoside, was measured spectrophotometrically at 400 nm. Inhibition of α-glucosidase was calculated:
